values
  ($$Barnet Museum$$, $$31 Wood Street Barnet London EN5 4BE$$, $$EN5 4BE$$, 51.652817, -0.202466, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=31%20Wood%20Street%20Barnet%20London%20EN5%204BE$$, $$http://www.barnetmuseum.co.uk/$$, $$http://www.barnetmuseum.co.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Barnet Museum Barnet Museum is a local history museum located in the London Borough of Barnet. It is housed in a beautiful 17th-century building, which was initially a private residence. The museum's collection reflects the rich history of the area, from prehistoric times to the present day. One of the highlights of the museum is its collection of Roman artefacts. Barnet was a significant Roman settlement, and the museum's collection includes pottery, coins, and other objects from this period. T$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/99/barnet-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/barnet-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/99/barnet-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Bourne Hall Museum$$, $$Spring Street Ewell Surrey KT17 1UF$$, $$KT17 1UF$$, 51.350377, -0.252282, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Spring%20Street%20Ewell%20Surrey%20KT17%201UF$$, $$http://www.epsom-ewell.gov.uk/EEBC/Leisure+and+Culture/Bourne+Hall/Museums+and+galleries/$$, $$http://www.epsom-ewell.gov.uk/EEBC/Leisure+and+Culture/Bourne+Hall/Museums+and+galleries/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Bourne Hall Museum Bourne Hall, situated in the heart of Ewell Village, is a remarkable modern building of unusual architectural interest, surrounded by beautiful grounds. Opened in 1970, it is well furnished, well equipped and flexible enough to accommodate most requirements. With a variety of different sized halls and rooms, it is perfect for anything from a small meeting to the largest of receptions. It is used for conferences, weddings and wedding receptions, fairs, recitals, meetings and pa$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/146/bourne-hall-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/bourne-hall-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/146/bourne-hall-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Burgh House, Hampstead Museum$$, $$Burgh House & Hampstead Museum New End Square Hampstead London NW3 1LT$$, $$NW3 1LT$$, 51.558181, -0.175068, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Burgh%20House%20%26%20Hampstead%20Museum%20New%20End%20Square%20Hampstead%20London%20NW3%201LT$$, $$http://www.burghhouse.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.burghhouse.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Burgh House, Hampstead Museum The Burgh House, located in the charming neighbourhood of Hampstead, is a museum and cultural centre steeped in history and brimming with character. The building itself dates back to 1704 and is a grade-1 listed, which means it is considered of exceptional interest and is one of the highest designations for a building in the UK. The house has a rich and varied past, having served as a private residence, a meeting place for artists and intellectuals, and a community $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/103/burgh-house-hampstead-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/burgh-house-hampstead-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/103/burgh-house-hampstead-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Cutty Sark Visitors Center$$, $$Cutty Sark Clipper Ship King William Walk Greenwich London SE10 9HT$$, $$SE10 9HT$$, 51.483529, -0.009594, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Cutty%20Sark%20Clipper%20Ship%20King%20William%20Walk%20Greenwich%20London%20SE10%209HT$$, $$http://www.rmg.co.uk/cuttysark$$, $$http://www.rmg.co.uk/cuttysark$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Waltham Forest$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Cutty Sark Visitors Center Visit the Cutty Sark Visitors Centre and enjoy a unique voyage of discovery as you step back in time and experience life on board the last surviving tea clipper. Learn about the stories that earned Cutty Sark her reputation as one of the world’s most famous sailing ships. Impressively positioned on the riverbank at Greenwich, the Cutty Sark Visitors Centre stands at the gateway to the UNESCO World Heritage Site of Maritime Greenwich, alongside attractions including the$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/217/cutty-sark-visitors-center$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/cutty-sark-visitors-center-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/217/cutty-sark-visitors-center$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Dr Johnson's House$$, $$Dr. Johnson's House 17 Cough Square City of London London EC4A 3DE$$, $$EC4A 3DE$$, 51.515155, -0.107765, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Dr.%20Johnson's%20House%2017%20Cough%20Square%20City%20of%20London%20London%20EC4A%203DE$$, $$http://www.drjohnsonshouse.org/$$, $$http://www.drjohnsonshouse.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Dr Johnson's House It was in the garret of this early 18th-century house that Dr Samuel Johnson compiled his famous Dictionary: a nine-year labour of love that resulted in the first comprehensive lexicon of the English language. The house has been restored to its condition during Johnson's 11-year occupancy (from 1748 to 1759) and retains many original features — including some heavy-duty crime prevention measures and an ingenious `cellarette' in the dining room. Arranged over several floors, th$$, $$Check museum website$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/51/dr-johnsons-house$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/dr-johnsons-house-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/51/dr-johnsons-house$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Fenton House$$, $$Hampstead Grove Hampstead London NW3 6SP$$, $$NW3 6SP$$, 51.558694, -0.179173, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Hampstead%20Grove%20Hampstead%20London%20NW3%206SP$$, $$http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/fenton-house/$$, $$http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/fenton-house/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Fenton House This beautiful 17th-century merchant's house is a hidden gem in London, a place of unique charm and ambience.Lady Binning bought the house in 1936 and filled it with her highly decorative collections of porcelain, Georgian furniture and 17th-century needlework. Known primarily for its collection of early keyboard instruments, this National Trust property also contains an interesting array of furniture, textiles, art and 18th-century porcelain. Interior design students will be intrig$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/102/fenton-house$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/fenton-house-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/102/fenton-house$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Forty Hall Museum$$, $$Forty Hall & Estate Forty Hill London EN2 9HA$$, $$EN2 9HA$$, 51.66979, -0.068542, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Forty%20Hall%20%26%20Estate%20Forty%20Hill%20London%20EN2%209HA$$, $$http://www.fortyhallestate.co.uk/$$, $$http://www.fortyhallestate.co.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Forty Hall Museum Forty Hall is a Grade 1 listed Jacobean Manor House, nestled in leafy Enfield and set amidst pleasure gardens, ancient royal parkland, majestic trees, lakes and watercourses. A venture in to the Hall promises to delight and impress. Our permanent exhibition tells the story of Forty Hall & Estate throughout the ages and looks at the life and times of Sir Nicholas Rainton and life in the seventeenth century. With a range of visual and audio interpretation and displays there are a$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/151/forty-hall-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/forty-hall-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/151/forty-hall-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Gunnersbury Park Museum$$, $$Gunnersbury Park House Popes Lane London W5 4NH$$, $$W5 4NH$$, 51.501391, -0.292648, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Gunnersbury%20Park%20House%20Popes%20Lane%20London%20W5%204NH$$, $$https://www.visitgunnersbury.org/$$, $$https://www.visitgunnersbury.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Gunnersbury Park Museum A fascinating historical attraction located in the London Borough of Hounslow. The Gunnersbury Park Museum is situated within the beautiful surroundings of Gunnersbury Park, a Grade II* listed park and garden that covers approximately 72 acres. The museum itself is housed in a beautiful Georgian mansion that was built in the late 18th century. The mansion was originally the home of the Rothschild family, and it was gifted to the local council in the 1930s by the Rothschil$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/4/gunnersbury-park-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/gunnersbury-park-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/4/gunnersbury-park-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Hackney Museum$$, $$1 Reading Lane London E8 1GQ$$, $$E8 1GQ$$, 51.544479, -0.05607, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=1%20Reading%20Lane%20London%20E8%201GQ$$, $$https://hackney-museum.hackney.gov.uk/$$, $$https://hackney-museum.hackney.gov.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Hackney$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Hackney Museum The Hackney Museum is a community history museum that serves the London Borough of Hackney. It holds and maintains a collection of over 8,500 objects, artworks, images, and oral history recordings. The collections reflect the daily lives of people in the borough, particularly those who have migrated from other parts of the world. We aim to provide a platform for under-represented voices to share their experiences and memories and create a safe and trustworthy space for local commu$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/139/hackney-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/hackney-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/139/hackney-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Ham House$$, $$Ham Street Richmond upon Thames London TW10 7RS$$, $$TW10 7RS$$, 51.44424, -0.314193, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ham%20Street%20Richmond%20upon%20Thames%20London%20TW10%207RS$$, $$http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/ham-house/$$, $$http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/ham-house/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Ham House This rare and atmospheric 17th-century house sits on the banks of the River Thames in Richmond. It is the creation of the tenacious Duchess of Lauderdale and her husband, the Duke, who together transformed Ham into one of the grandest Stuart houses in England. Ham House is internationally recognised for its superb collection of paintings, furniture and textiles, largely acquired 400 years ago. Some of our unique objects include a rare Chinese teapot, said to have been used by the Duche$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/154/ham-house$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/ham-house-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/154/ham-house$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Hogarth's House$$, $$Hogarth Lane, Great West Road London W4 2QN$$, $$W4 2QN$$, 51.487099, -0.258815, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Hogarth%20Lane%2C%20Great%20West%20Road%20London%20W4%202QN$$, $$http://www.hounslow.info/arts-culture/historic-houses-museums/hogarth-house/the-museum/$$, $$http://www.hounslow.info/arts-culture/historic-houses-museums/hogarth-house/the-museum/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Hogarth's House Hogarth's House, built around 1700, was the country home of the great painter, engraver and satirist William Hogarth (1697-1764) from 1749 until his death. Hogarth's town house, in what is now Leicester Square, was demolished in 1870. Fortunately his rural retreat in Chiswick - where he lived with his wife, mother-in-law and sister - has survived, and is now an oasis in busy West London. Set behind old brick walls with a delightful garden containing Hogarth's mulberry tree – the $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/114/hogarths-house$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/hogarths-house-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/114/hogarths-house$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Honeywood Museum$$, $$Honeywood Walk Carshalton Sutton London SM5 3NX$$, $$SM5 3NX$$, 51.365998, -0.165867, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Honeywood%20Walk%20Carshalton%20Sutton%20London%20SM5%203NX$$, $$https://friendsofhoneywood.co.uk/$$, $$https://friendsofhoneywood.co.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Honeywood Museum Nestled beside the tranquil waters of Carshalton Ponds, Honeywood Museum is a hidden gem that offers a delightful journey through time. This Grade II listed building, with its charming chalk and flint façade, stands as a testament to centuries of local history and architectural evolution.​. A Stroll Through Time Originally constructed in the mid-17th century, Honeywood began as a modest dwelling known as Wandle Cottage. Over the years, it underwent several transformations, most $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/225/honeywood-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/honeywood-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/225/honeywood-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Islington Museum$$, $$245 St John St Islington London EC1V 4NB$$, $$EC1V 4NB$$, 51.526488, -0.104527, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=245%20St%20John%20St%20Islington%20London%20EC1V%204NB$$, $$http://www.islington.gov.uk/islington/history-heritage/heritage_museum/Pages/default.aspx?extra=9$$, $$http://www.islington.gov.uk/islington/history-heritage/heritage_museum/Pages/default.aspx?extra=9$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Islington$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Islington Museum Nestled just a few steps below the surface in the heart of Clerkenwell, Islington Museum invites visitors to step into a vivid world of stories that shaped one of London's most diverse and dynamic boroughs. Though modest in size, this museum is brimming with personality, passion, and local pride—a real treasure trove for anyone curious about Islington's rich past and the people who've called it home. As you walk through its welcoming entrance, you'll find yourself drawn into a t$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/69/islington-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/islington-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/69/islington-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Kenwood$$, $$The Iveagh Bequest Kenwood House Hampstead Ln Barnet London NW3 7JR$$, $$NW3 7JR$$, 51.571328, -0.1676, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The%20Iveagh%20Bequest%20Kenwood%20House%20Hampstead%20Ln%20Barnet%20London%20NW3%207JR$$, $$http://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=5928&awinaffid=272699&clickref=Kenwood&p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.english-heritage.org.uk%2Fvisit%2Fplaces%2Fkenwood%2F$$, $$http://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=5928&awinaffid=272699&clickref=Kenwood&p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.english-heritage.org.uk%2Fvisit%2Fplaces%2Fkenwood%2F$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Kenwood Kenwood is among the finest of all up English Heritage's Great houses. The vividly re-presented interiors and collections, and the improved the visitor's facilities, create a relaxed atmosphere. For families there's an enjoyable activity based in the Orangery. Enhance features include the re-presentation of the wonderful Adam rooms; The re-display of the famous Iveagh collection of paintings; and imaginative interpretation for visitors of all ages. Relaxed and welcoming, Kenwood is more $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/104/kenwood$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/kenwood-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/104/kenwood$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$London Canal Museum$$, $$12-13 New Wharf Rd Islington London N1 9RT$$, $$N1 9RT$$, 51.534223, -0.120297, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=12-13%20New%20Wharf%20Rd%20Islington%20London%20N1%209RT$$, $$https://www.canalmuseum.org.uk/$$, $$https://www.canalmuseum.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Islington$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$London Canal Museum The London Canal Museum is just a five-minute walk from King’s Cross station but you could almost be in another world. The museum occupies a historic waterside building beside the picturesque urban beauty spot that is Battlebridge Basin, once used by industry and nowadays home to many colourful boats. The museum tells the story of all aspects of London’s canals. You can walk inside a residential narrow boat cabin, and imagine the life of the thousands of families who lived on$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/7/london-canal-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/london-canal-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/7/london-canal-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$London Museum of Water and Steam$$, $$London Museum of Water & Steam Green Dragon Lane Brentford London TW8 0EN$$, $$TW8 0EN$$, 51.489526, -0.289908, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=London%20Museum%20of%20Water%20%26%20Steam%20Green%20Dragon%20Lane%20Brentford%20London%20TW8%200EN$$, $$https://waterandsteam.org.uk/$$, $$https://waterandsteam.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$London Museum of Water and Steam The London Museum of Water & Steam (formerly Kew Bridge Steam Museum) is one of London’s most significant Victorian visitor attractions. It houses some of the world’s rarest working steam engines still in their original location and tells the incredible story of how the Victorians cleaned up London’s water supply – and in doing so created the blue print for the modern city of London as we know it today. The new Waterworks Gallery takes you on a journey through ti$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/6/london-museum-of-water-and-steam$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/london-museum-of-water-and-steam-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/6/london-museum-of-water-and-steam$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$London Transport Museum$$, $$London Transport Musuem Covent Garden Piazza London WC2E 7BB$$, $$WC2E 7BB$$, 51.512125, -0.121222, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=London%20Transport%20Musuem%20Covent%20Garden%20Piazza%20London%20WC2E%207BB$$, $$https://www.ltmuseum.co.uk/$$, $$https://www.ltmuseum.co.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$London Transport Museum The London Transport Museum is an often-overlooked jewel in the heart of London. Travel through three stories and over 200 years of history covering the amazing evolution of public transport in London, as well as the social history, engineering, architecture and design that grew and changed alongside it. Located at the edge of the Covent Garden Piazza, the London Transport Museum is nestled inside the historic Flower Market, a Grade II listed building built back in 1670. $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/8/london-transport-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/london-transport-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/8/london-transport-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Museum of Croydon$$, $$Central Library Katharine St Croydon CR9 1ET$$, $$CR9 1ET$$, 51.371911, -0.099511, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Central%20Library%20Katharine%20St%20Croydon%20CR9%201ET$$, $$http://www.museumofcroydon.com/$$, $$http://www.museumofcroydon.com/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Museum of Croydon The Museum of Croydon exists to collect, conserve and interpret Croydon's cultural heritage, so that everyone can take part in creative and enjoyable learning experiences. The Museum of Croydon Gallery reveals the history of Croydon from 1800 to Now, through the objects and stories of local people. The Riesco Gallery displays over 200 items from Raymond Riesco’s personal collection of Chinese ceramics, alongside more than 60 objects from our Roman and Anglo-Saxon collections. T$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/163/museum-of-croydon$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/museum-of-croydon-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/163/museum-of-croydon$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Museum of London Docklands$$, $$No.1 Warehouse West India Quay London E14 4AL$$, $$E14 4AL$$, 51.507613, -0.024539, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=No.1%20Warehouse%20West%20India%20Quay%20London%20E14%204AL$$, $$http://www.museumoflondon.org.uk/docklands/$$, $$http://www.museumoflondon.org.uk/docklands/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Museum of London Docklands Located in the heart of the historical East London's Docklands, this museum is packed with exciting exhibits and interactive displays that explore the rich history of London's docks. From Roman times to the present day. One of the museum's standout exhibits is "London, Sugar & Slavery," which delves into the city's role in the transatlantic slave trade and the impact it had on the economy and culture. You'll find a range of artefacts and interactive displays, including$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/10/museum-of-london-docklands$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/museum-of-london-docklands-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/10/museum-of-london-docklands$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Museum of Richmond$$, $$Whittaker Ave Richmond-upon-Thames Surrey TW9 1TP$$, $$TW9 1TP$$, 51.458832, -0.306515, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Whittaker%20Ave%20Richmond-upon-Thames%20Surrey%20TW9%201TP$$, $$http://www.museumofrichmond.com/$$, $$http://www.museumofrichmond.com/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Museum of Richmond For centuries Richmond has been a centre of fashion and the arts, as well as home to several of Britain’s monarchs. Formerly the historical borough of Shene, Richmond was founded following King Henry VII’s building of Richmond Palace in the 16th century, named after the King’s earldom in Richmond, North Yorkshire. Even before the building of the Palace, the area had long been a seat of the monarchy and the elite, ranging from King Henry I to King Richard II. The re-establishme$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/164/museum-of-richmond$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/museum-of-richmond-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/164/museum-of-richmond$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Natural History Museum$$, $$Cromwell Rd Kensingston London SW7 5BD$$, $$SW7 5BD$$, 51.496564, -0.176868, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Cromwell%20Rd%20Kensingston%20London%20SW7%205BD$$, $$http://www.nhm.ac.uk/$$, $$http://www.nhm.ac.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Natural History Museum The museum is home to life and earth science specimens comprising some 80 million items within five main collections: botany, entomology, mineralogy, palaeontology and zoology. The museum is a world-renowned centre of research specialising in taxonomy, identification and conservation. Given the age of the institution, many of the collections have great historical as well as scientific value, such as specimens collected by Charles Darwin . The museum is particularly famous $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/78/natural-history-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/natural-history-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/78/natural-history-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Pollock's Toy Museum$$, $$1 Scala Street London W1T 2HL$$, $$W1T 2HL$$, 51.520335, -0.135284, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=1%20Scala%20Street%20London%20W1T%202HL$$, $$http://pollockstoys.com/$$, $$http://pollockstoys.com/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Pollock's Toy Museum The history begins in about 1856 in Hoxton, an area of London bordered by the wealth of the City and the poverty of the East End. This is where Benjamin Pollock was born. At this time the toy theatre trade was flourishing. But by the time Benjamin Pollock had married Eliza Redington and inherited her father's Theatrical Print Warehouse, the toy theatre trade had been overshadowed by new novelties such as ‘magic lanterns’ and ‘gramophones’. However Mr Pollock, in his dark and$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/82/pollocks-toy-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/pollocks-toy-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/82/pollocks-toy-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Redbridge Museum$$, $$Ilford Central Library Clements Road,Ilford, Essex IG1 1EA$$, $$IG1 1EA$$, 51.558064, 0.075328, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ilford%20Central%20Library%20Clements%20Road%2CIlford%2C%20Essex%20IG1%201EA$$, $$http://www.redbridge.gov.uk/museum$$, $$http://www.redbridge.gov.uk/museum$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Redbridge Museum Redbridge Museum was opened in 2000 and serves as the local community museum for the London Borough of Redbridge. The museum explores the many different places, people and events in over 150,000 years of local Redbridge history. The display items timeline spans from prehistoric animals to recent developments, with particular focus on the development of Ilford, Wanstead and Woodford from 1850s - 1950s. Regularly changing temporary exhibitions on local subjects complement the perm$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/169/redbridge-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/redbridge-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/169/redbridge-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Royal Observatory Greenwich and Peter Harrison Planetarium$$, $$Royal Observatory Greenwich Blackheath Ave London SE10 8XJ$$, $$SE10 8XJ$$, 51.477346, -0.000848, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Royal%20Observatory%20Greenwich%20Blackheath%20Ave%20London%20SE10%208XJ$$, $$http://www.rmg.co.uk/royal-observatory$$, $$http://www.rmg.co.uk/royal-observatory$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Waltham Forest$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Royal Observatory Greenwich and Peter Harrison Planetarium Think of a planetarium as a tour bus of the Universe taking you on amazing journeys to explore and experience the wonders of the night sky. Combining real images from spacecraft and telescopes with advanced CGI, all projected onto a fully immersive dome, the Planetarium can fly you into the heart of the Sun, transport you to distant galaxies, show you the birth of a star or land you on Mars. The Peter Harrison Planetarium at the Royal Ob$$, $$Check museum website$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/134/royal-observatory-greenwich-and-peter-harrison-planetarium$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/royal-observatory-greenwich-and-peter-harrison-planetarium-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/134/royal-observatory-greenwich-and-peter-harrison-planetarium$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Science Museum$$, $$Exhibition Road, South Kensington, London SW7 2DD$$, $$SW7 2DD$$, 51.497296, -0.176493, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Exhibition%20Road%2C%20South%20Kensington%2C%20London%20SW7%202DD$$, $$http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Science Museum The Science Museum features seven floors of educational and entertaining exhibits, including the Apollo 10 command module and a flight simulator. The Wellcome Wing showcases developments in contemporary science, medicine and technology. The Medical History Gallery in the museum's attic contains a substantial collection of medical history treasures. Pattern Pod introduces under-eights to the importance of patterns in contemporary science and Launch Pad is a popular hands-on gallery$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/218/science-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/science-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/218/science-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The British Museum$$, $$Great Russell Street London WC1B 3DG$$, $$WC1B 3DG$$, 51.519364, -0.126848, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Great%20Russell%20Street%20London%20WC1B%203DG$$, $$http://www.britishmuseum.org/$$, $$http://www.britishmuseum.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The British Museum The British Museum, in central London is considered to be one of the world's greatest museums of human history and culture. With artefacts ranging from small archaeological fragments to massive objects, the museums' collection is said to be amongst the finest, most comprehensive, and largest in existence. Items from Africa, Asia, Europe, the Americas and the Ancient World, illustrate and document the story of human culture from its beginnings to the modern day. The British Mus$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/25/the-british-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-british-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/25/the-british-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Brunel Museum$$, $$Brunel Museum Railway Avenue Rotherhithe London SE16 4LF$$, $$SE16 4LF$$, 51.501596, -0.05294, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Brunel%20Museum%20Railway%20Avenue%20Rotherhithe%20London%20SE16%204LF$$, $$http://www.brunel-museum.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.brunel-museum.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Newham$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Brunel Museum The Engine House was designed by Sir Marc Isambard Brunel to be part of the infrastructure of the Thames Tunnel. It held steam-powered pumps used to extract water from the tunnel. Since 1961 the building has been used as a museum displaying information on the construction of the tunnel and the other projects by Marc and Isambard Kingdom Brunel. Structural decay was prevented in 1975 by a charitable trust named "Brunel Exhibition Rotherhithe". In 2006 the museum changed its name$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/220/the-brunel-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-brunel-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/220/the-brunel-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Cartoon Museum$$, $$63 Wells Street London W1T 3PZ$$, $$W1T 3PZ$$, 51.517443, -0.138371, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=63%20Wells%20Street%20London%20W1T%203PZ$$, $$http://www.cartoonmuseum.org/$$, $$http://www.cartoonmuseum.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Cartoon Museum Tucked away in the heart of historic Bloomsbury, the Cartoon Museum displays a vibrant array of original art from the 1800s to the modern day: cartoons, comics, caricatures and much more. As the home of British cartooning, the museum is the only place of its kind in the UK dedicated to collecting and displaying original British cartoons and comics. In 1988 a group of cartoonists, collectors and lovers of the art form came together as The Cartoon Art Trust with the aim of found$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/26/the-cartoon-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-cartoon-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/26/the-cartoon-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Charterhouse$$, $$Charterhouse Square Barbican London EC1M 6AN$$, $$EC1M 6AN$$, 51.521938, -0.100709, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Charterhouse%20Square%20Barbican%20London%20EC1M%206AN$$, $$https://thecharterhouse.org/$$, $$https://thecharterhouse.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Charterhouse The Charterhouse is a historic landmark in London that has played a significant role in the City's history for over 600 years. Situated in the heart of Clerkenwell, the Charterhouse is a complex of buildings that includes a chapel, a library, and a museum. Originally founded as a Carthusian monastery in the 14th century, the site has been used for various purposes, including as a private mansion, a school, and an almshouse. The history of the Charterhouse dates back to the 14th $$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/229/the-charterhouse$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-charterhouse-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/229/the-charterhouse$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Faraday Museum$$, $$The Royal Institution of Great Britain 21 Albemarle Street Mayfair London W1S 4BS$$, $$W1S 4BS$$, 51.509947, -0.142554, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The%20Royal%20Institution%20of%20Great%20Britain%2021%20Albemarle%20Street%20Mayfair%20London%20W1S%204BS$$, $$http://www.rigb.org/museum$$, $$http://www.rigb.org/museum$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Faraday Museum The 200-year-old plus organisation worthily dedicated to educating the general public about the latest scientific developments. With an illustrious history and 14 Nobel Prize winners to its name, the Royal Institute has a lot to shout about and it does so with some panache. The museum trumpets some of the scientific greats who have worked in this building, including Humphry Davy (he of the miner's lamp), James Dewar (he of the flask) and the museum's namesake, Michael Faraday,$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/53/the-faraday-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-faraday-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/53/the-faraday-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Golden Hinde$$, $$Golden Hinde St Mary Overie Dock Cathedral Street London SE1 9DE$$, $$SE1 9DE$$, 51.50626, -0.090481, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Golden%20Hinde%20St%20Mary%20Overie%20Dock%20Cathedral%20Street%20London%20SE1%209DE$$, $$https://www.goldenhinde.co.uk/$$, $$https://www.goldenhinde.co.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Golden Hinde Experience the life of a 16th century explorer aboard The Golden Hinde , a full-sized reconstruction of the ship Sir Francis Drake used to circumnavigate the globe between 1577-80. Located in St Mary Overie Dock, London Bankside, The Golden Hinde is a full-sized authentic reconstruction of the original ship. Built in the 1970s to commemorate the 400th anniversary of Drake claiming California for Queen Elizabeth 1st, 17th June 1579. She was a working ship which has travelled much$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/59/the-golden-hinde$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-golden-hinde-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/59/the-golden-hinde$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Horniman Museum & Gardens$$, $$Horniman Museum & Gardens 100 London Rd Forest Hill London SE23 3PQ$$, $$SE23 3PQ$$, 51.441131, -0.060737, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Horniman%20Museum%20%26%20Gardens%20100%20London%20Rd%20Forest%20Hill%20London%20SE23%203PQ$$, $$http://www.horniman.ac.uk/$$, $$http://www.horniman.ac.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Horniman Museum & Gardens Frederick John Horniman, Victorian tea trader and philanthropist, began collecting objects, specimens and artefacts 'illustrating natural history and the arts and handicrafts of various peoples of the world' from around 1860. His overarching mission was to 'bring the world to Forest Hill' and educate and enrich the lives of the local community. That collection has since grown to over 300,000 objects. 80,000 anthropology specimens from around the world, including art$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/130/the-horniman-museum-gardens$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-horniman-museum-gardens-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/130/the-horniman-museum-gardens$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Museum of Fulham Palace$$, $$Fulham Palace Bishop's Ave Fulham London SW6 6EA$$, $$SW6 6EA$$, 51.470771, -0.21588, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Fulham%20Palace%20Bishop's%20Ave%20Fulham%20London%20SW6%206EA$$, $$http://www.fulhampalace.org/$$, $$http://www.fulhampalace.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Museum of Fulham Palace The Museum of Fulham Palace charts the long history of the Fulham Palace site, from Prehistoric times and Roman settlement, through Medieval, Tudor, Georgian and Victorian bishops to the present day. The Museum Collection includes paintings, archaeology and artefacts, as well as the Palace itself, as demonstrated by a fascinating 1:50 scale model of the building. The collection is permanently displayed in two rooms of the Palace which have been restored to their origi$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/117/the-museum-of-fulham-palace$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-museum-of-fulham-palace-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/117/the-museum-of-fulham-palace$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Postal Museum$$, $$Phoenix Place London WC1X 0DA$$, $$WC1X 0DA$$, 51.524762, -0.114056, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Phoenix%20Place%20London%20WC1X%200DA$$, $$https://www.postalmuseum.org/$$, $$https://www.postalmuseum.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Postal Museum The Postal Museum is a fascinating destination for anyone interested in the history of communication and the role of the postal service in society. Located in the heart of London, the museum offers a wealth of information and interactive exhibits that explore the rich history of the postal system in the United Kingdom and beyond. The museum traces its roots back to the early days of the Royal Mail, which was established in the 16th century under the reign of King Henry VIII. Ov$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/223/the-postal-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-postal-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/223/the-postal-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Ragged School Museum$$, $$Ragged School Museum 46-50 Copperfield Rd London E3 4RR$$, $$E3 4RR$$, 51.519458, -0.035875, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Ragged%20School%20Museum%2046-50%20Copperfield%20Rd%20London%20E3%204RR$$, $$http://www.raggedschoolmuseum.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.raggedschoolmuseum.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Ragged School Museum The Ragged School Museum in London is a unique and fascinating museum that tells the story of the ragged schools of the 19th century. These schools were established to provide education for poor and working-class children who were not able to attend regular schools. The museum is located in a building that was once the largest ragged school in London and provides a glimpse into the lives of these children and the educators who taught them. The museum is housed in a group$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/140/the-ragged-school-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-ragged-school-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/140/the-ragged-school-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Stephens Collection$$, $$Avenue House 17 East End Road London N3 3QE$$, $$N3 3QE$$, 51.59687, -0.196229, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Avenue%20House%2017%20East%20End%20Road%20London%20N3%203QE$$, $$http://www.stephenshouseandgardens.com/$$, $$http://www.stephenshouseandgardens.com/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Stephens Collection The boutique museum that tells the life story of Henry ‘Inky’ Stephens. With fascinating artefacts and memorabilia from the history of the man, to his business and his passions. Dr. Henry Stephens was the inventor (in 1832) of the famous "Blue-Black Writing Fluid", later developed into ink. The family firm manufacturing the ink and various accessories lay the foundations of a considerable family fortune. His son, Henry Charles Stephens, continued the development of the fa$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/109/the-stephens-collection$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-stephens-collection-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/109/the-stephens-collection$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$The Wimbledon Lawn Tennis Museum$$, $$Wimbledon Lawn Tennis Museum Church Road Wimbledon London SW19 5AE$$, $$SW19 5AE$$, 51.416892, -0.21329, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Wimbledon%20Lawn%20Tennis%20Museum%20Church%20Road%20Wimbledon%20London%20SW19%205AE$$, $$http://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/museum_and_tours/201205091336567035518.html$$, $$http://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/museum_and_tours/201205091336567035518.html$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$The Wimbledon Lawn Tennis Museum The Wimbledon Lawn Tennis Museum is a must-see destination for any tennis fan visiting London. Located within the grounds of the All England Lawn Tennis and Croquet Club, the museum offers a fascinating insight into the history and traditions of the Wimbledon championships, the oldest and most prestigious tennis tournament in the world. Upon entering the museum, visitors are greeted by a large collection of rackets, balls, and other tennis memorabilia, spanning t$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/17/the-wimbledon-lawn-tennis-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/the-wimbledon-lawn-tennis-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/17/the-wimbledon-lawn-tennis-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Twinings Museum$$, $$The Twinings Museum 216 The Strand London WC2R 1AP$$, $$WC2R 1AP$$, 51.513089, -0.112967, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The%20Twinings%20Museum%20216%20The%20Strand%20London%20WC2R%201AP$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/189/twinings-museum$$, null, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Twinings Museum The Twinings Museum is a small museum adjacent to Twinings Shop at 216, The Strand, London, England. Twinings is thought to be the oldest company in London to have traded continuously on the same site with the same family since its foundation. It was founded by Thomas Twining (1675-1741) who bought an old coffee house in 1706. He daringly introduced tea — then an exotic drink enjoyed by the wealthy — and in 1717 opened the Golden Lyon to sell tea and coffee. In 1787, his grandson$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/189/twinings-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/twinings-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/189/twinings-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$V & A Museum of Childhood$$, $$V&A Museum of Childhood Cambridge Heath Rd Hackney London E2 9PA$$, $$E2 9PA$$, 51.527774, -0.055182, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=V%26A%20Museum%20of%20Childhood%20Cambridge%20Heath%20Rd%20Hackney%20London%20E2%209PA$$, $$http://www.vam.ac.uk/moc$$, $$http://www.vam.ac.uk/moc$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Hackney$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$V & A Museum of Childhood Welcoming over 400,000 visitors through its doors every year, the V&A Museum of Childhood in London's Bethnal Green houses the Victoria and Albert Museum's collection of childhood-related objects and artefacts, spanning the 1600s to the present day. With a fine collection of children's clothes and paraphernalia like high-chairs and prams, the museum also illustrates the social history of childhood — but few will be able to resist embarking on a quest to rediscover the t$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/143/v-a-museum-of-childhood$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/v-a-museum-of-childhood-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/143/v-a-museum-of-childhood$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$V&A (Victoria & Albert) Museum$$, $$Victoria and Albert Museum Cromwell Road South Kensington London SW7 2RL$$, $$SW7 2RL$$, 51.496941, -0.172199, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20Cromwell%20Road%20South%20Kensington%20London%20SW7%202RL$$, $$http://www.vam.ac.uk/$$, $$http://www.vam.ac.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$V&A (Victoria & Albert) Museum The Victoria and Albert Museum (often abbreviated as the V&A) is the world's largest museum of decorative arts and design. Housing a permanent collection of over 4.5 million objects. It was founded in 1852 and named after Queen Victoria and Prince Albert. The V&A is located in the Brompton district of the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea, in an area that has become known as "Albertopolis" because of its association with Prince Albert, the Albert Memorial and$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/178/va-victoria-albert-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/va-victoria-albert-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/178/va-victoria-albert-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Wellcome Collection Museum$$, $$Wellcome Collection 183 Euston Rd Camden London NW1 2BE$$, $$NW1 2BE$$, 51.525898, -0.133918, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Wellcome%20Collection%20183%20Euston%20Rd%20Camden%20London%20NW1%202BE$$, $$http://www.wellcomecollection.org/$$, $$http://www.wellcomecollection.org/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Wellcome Collection Museum The Wellcome Collection Museum, named after pioneering 19th century pharmacist Sir Henry Wellcome, is the destination for the incurably curious. The Medicine Man gallery introduces the visitor to Henry Wellcome — an extraordinary character whose entrepreneurial flair took him from humble American log cabin origins to millionaire pharmaceutical business giant and philanthropist. Along the way Wellcome also found time to run major archaeological digs, pioneer aerial phot$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/179/wellcome-collection-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/wellcome-collection-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/179/wellcome-collection-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$William Morris Gallery$$, $$Lloyd Park Forest Rd London E17 4PP$$, $$E17 4PP$$, 51.590586, -0.018517, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Lloyd%20Park%20Forest%20Rd%20London%20E17%204PP$$, $$http://www.wmgallery.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.wmgallery.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$Waltham Forest$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$William Morris Gallery The William Morris Gallery is housed in a Georgian house, built in the 1740s and set in Lloyd Park in Walthamstow, in north-east London. The grade II* listed building was Morris's family home from 1848 to 1856. The only public Gallery devoted to William Morris, it reopened in August 2012 following a major redevelopment. This award-winning museum celebrates William Morris, the founding father of the Arts and Crafts Movement. A powerhouse of energy and creativity, Morris was$$, $$Free$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/144/william-morris-gallery$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/william-morris-gallery-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/144/william-morris-gallery$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$),
  ($$Wimbledon Windmill Museum$$, $$Windmill Rd Wimbledon London SW19 5NR$$, $$SW19 5NR$$, 51.436949, -0.231888, $$Museums & culture$$, $$10:00$$, $$17:00$$, $$https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Windmill%20Rd%20Wimbledon%20London%20SW19%205NR$$, $$http://www.wimbledonwindmill.org.uk/$$, $$http://www.wimbledonwindmill.org.uk/$$, 5, null, 0, $$Families and children$$, $$London$$, '{}', $$Check opening hours before travelling.$$, $$Wimbledon Windmill Museum A visit to Wimbledon Windmill Museum followed by a bracing walk on the Commons and refreshment at the Windmill Tearooms makes an excellent day out for both family and adults. The Commons are only a short distance from central London and can be reached by public transport. Since 1817 the windmill has been a distinctive landmark in the middle of Wimbledon Common. It operated until 1864, when the 5th Earl Spencer evicted the miller as part of his plan to enclose the common$$, $$Check museum website$$, false, $$Museums London child-friendly listing$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/138/wimbledon-windmill-museum$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/img/wimbledon-windmill-museum-320x308@2x.jpg$$, $$https://www.museumslondon.org/museum/138/wimbledon-windmill-museum$$, $$other$$, $$weekly$$, $$published$$)
